Hide the in-game dialogue window when the HUD is hidden via "Hide UI", so the
companion (bottom-screen) dialogue UI is the sole conversation surface while
Hide UI is active; restore it when Hide UI is toggled back on.

Unlike the HUD (mHud) and the tooltip layer (mToolTips), the dialogue window's
visibility is NOT driven by updateVisible() at all in vanilla — it is toggled by
GuiModeState::update(visible) on GM_Dialogue push/pop, so Hide UI currently has
no effect on it. We add the gate here, in updateVisible() (which setHudVisibility
calls right after flipping mHudEnabled), because this is the single place the
Hide UI state is applied to windows.

Gate choice — getMode() == GM_Dialogue, NOT containsMode() and NOT isVisible():
  * isVisible() cannot restore the window: once we hide it, isVisible() is stuck
    false, so (mHudEnabled && isVisible()) can never become true again when Hide
    UI is toggled back on — the window would stay gone for the rest of the
    conversation.
  * containsMode(GM_Dialogue) is too broad: GM_Dialogue stays on the mode stack
    while a service window (Barter/Spells/Travel/...) is pushed on top. Vanilla
    hides the dialogue window during barter (the pushed mode calls the previous
    mode's GuiModeState::update(false)); a containsMode gate would force it back
    visible behind/over the service window every updateVisible().
  * getMode() == GM_Dialogue is exactly the condition under which vanilla shows
    the dialogue window (dialogue is the topmost/active mode). When a service
    window is pushed, getMode() is no longer GM_Dialogue, so we leave the window
    alone and vanilla's own hide stands — no barter/service regression.

Hiding mid-conversation is safe: WindowBase::setVisible(false) calls onClose(),
but DialogueWindow::onClose() early-returns while containsMode(GM_Dialogue) is
true (see companion-dialogue-export.patch), so it neither clears mHistoryContents
nor emits COMPANION_DIALOGUE_CLOSED. setVisible(true) re-shows it (onOpen is a
base no-op for DialogueWindow), so toggling Hide UI off restores the exact same
open conversation.

--- a/apps/openmw/mwgui/windowmanagerimp.cpp
+++ b/apps/openmw/mwgui/windowmanagerimp.cpp
@@ -648,6 +648,16 @@
         mHud->setVisible(mHudEnabled && !loading);
         // COMPANION: keep floating actor-name tooltips visible even when the HUD is
         // hidden via the Hide UI toggle. update() only shows the focus-object name.
         mToolTips->setVisible(!loading);

+        // COMPANION: hide the dialogue window with Hide UI so the companion (bottom)
+        // screen handles all dialogue interaction; restore it when Hide UI is toggled
+        // off (mHudEnabled true). Gated on getMode()==GM_Dialogue — the exact condition
+        // under which vanilla shows the window (a pushed service window makes it no
+        // longer the top mode, so this leaves it alone during barter/spells/travel).
+        // onClose() is a no-op while GM_Dialogue is still on the stack, so hiding it
+        // mid-conversation does not end the dialogue or clear its history.
+        if (mDialogueWindow && getMode() == GM_Dialogue)
+            mDialogueWindow->setVisible(mHudEnabled && !loading);
+
         bool gameMode = !isGuiMode();
